# Smart Wearable Device for Toddlers

This innovative smart wearable device is designed to enhance the safety of toddlers by preventing sexual abuse.  
The device is equipped with a flex sensor (or Velostat) that detects abnormal physical contact, triggering real-time notifications to parents or guardians through a cloud-based app (Blynk).  
This proactive solution empowers parents to respond immediately to potential threats, ensuring child safety in various environments.  

The patent showcases my commitment to innovative safety solutions and the integration of IoT technology to address critical societal challenges.

